The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 January is 19,765 (2,287.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 December, there were 4,158 new confirmed cases (481.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 December, there were 2,621 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 59% (1,537 extra cases).
